rComments: Nice professor, but assignment heavy course. Written exam is math heavy.
Great professor. Demanding but worth it

He is a part-time professor, works full-time with IBM. He covers essentially important aspects of computational finance. Assignments are tough - yes, be prepared to spend long hours, but is quite fair in grading. Could be clearer in lectures, as his slides seem incomplete.

He has a great intro course on data science and machine learning. He pushes the class to research various APIs and algorithms and present them in groups. At the same time he doesn't make it super complicated. Very interesting course.

Great prof! His material is always interesting. I really liked the group presentations which provided an opportunity to cover a larger range of topics which are not being covered in the course in detail.
